The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Mahindra may move to city

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Following an initiative taken by the Indian Football Association (IFA), Mahindra United may shift base from Mumbai to Calcutta. 

For quiet some time the Mumbai outfit has been looking for a bigger and stronger support base, for which Calcutta has remained on top of their priority list. 

According to IFA secretary Subroto Dutta, the associations constitution has a provision to invite any teams financed and run by a corporate ?? based outside West Bengal??? to play in the local league. 

Keeping this in mind, the IFA is planning to have Mahindra United in the CFL Premier Division (won by Mohun Bagan in the inaugural year). 

